They all do roughly the same thing: you type something, they respond. They all have free tiers that are genuinely useful, and they all have paid tiers around £15 a month if you want more capacity and access to better models. The pricing is essentially identical.

But they're not interchangeable. They've each developed real strengths over the last year, and using the right one for the right job makes a noticeable difference.

**Claude** is the one we use most at Kelvinstone. It's made by Anthropic, and it's generally considered the strongest at writing quality, working with long documents, and accuracy. It hallucinates less than the others — meaning it's less likely to confidently make things up. If you're going to use one tool primarily, this is the one we'd recommend, especially if your work involves a lot of writing, contracts, or anything where being wrong has consequences.

